{
  "name": "Red Velvet Protein Cookies (Oat Base)",
  "description": "Lean oat-flour red velvet with a protein cream-cheese frosting (frosting is a sub_recipe pin). The oat-base branch of the red velvet bake-off, rehabbed from the original floppy version for structure: pumpkin cut 0.5 -> 0.25 cup, oat flour doubled 0.25 -> 0.5 cup, cornstarch dropped, baking soda halved, an egg white added for set, and baked lower-and-longer (325F, 15-18 min). Yogurt kept for tang and protein. Sibling branch is the Crumbl-base version; bake both and promote the winner. Standalone root. Untested at this formulation.",
  "tags": [
    "crumbl",
    "cookie",
    "protein",
    "red-velvet"
  ],
  "yield": {
    "amount": 5,
    "unit": "cookies"
  },
  "content": {
    "steps": [
      {
        "componentKey": "c1",
        "order": 1,
        "section": "Cookie",
        "temperature": 325,
        "instructionText": "Preheat oven to 325F. Line a tray with parchment."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "c2",
        "order": 2,
        "section": "Cookie",
        "instructionText": "Whisk the wets - yogurt, pumpkin, egg, egg white, vanilla, food coloring, vinegar - then stir in the Splenda."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "c3",
        "order": 3,
        "section": "Cookie",
        "instructionText": "Add the dries - cocoa, oat flour, pudding, protein, baking soda, salt. Mix to a thick dough."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "c4",
        "order": 4,
        "section": "Cookie",
        "instructionText": "Rest 10-15 min to hydrate. If still batter-like, add oat flour 1 tbsp at a time until scoopable."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "c5",
        "order": 5,
        "section": "Cookie",
        "instructionText": "Scoop 5 cookies and shape into pucks (they barely spread). Bake 15-18 min at 325F until the tops spring back to a light touch and the edges are set."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "c6",
        "order": 6,
        "section": "Cookie",
        "instructionText": "Cool fully on the tray - they firm up as they cool."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "f1",
        "order": 7,
        "section": "Frosting",
        "instructionText": "Beat the yogurt, cream cheese, protein, and Splenda smooth. Add pudding mix to thicken, or chill 20-30 min. Frost the cooled cookies."
      }
    ],
